AND YOU MUSTN'T BE.
YOUR MOTHER
WOULDN'T LIKE
THAT, WOULD SHE?
NO.
NO. WELL,
THEN YOU MUST BE
A LOT NICER TO ME.
NOW...
YOU PUT THIS
AROUND YOUR NECK...
AND EVERY DAY
YOU WEAR IT,
YOU'LL BE BLESSED.
WEAR IT
NEXT TO YOUR WARM
LITTLE HEART.
IT'S BEATING
SO FAST.
YOU KNOW...
IT REMINDS ME
OF A LITTLE BIRD
I ONCE HELD
IN MY HAND.
IT WAS SO AFRAID
I'D HURT IT,
BUT I DIDN'T.
THAT'S ALL I
WANTED TO SAY
TO YOU.
THANK YOU, FATHER.
MARIA, IT'S
YOUR BEDTIME.
